    "body": "This PR adds two new benchmarking files that compares\r\na - Pytorch nn.RMSNorm\r\nb - TorchCompile RMSNorm\r\nc - Quack RMSNorm\r\n\r\nFor both forward and backward passes.  \r\n\r\nUses triton.do_bench with timing based benchmarking rather than num iters.  \r\nThis clears the L2 cache, and in theory provides more accurate results than iter based.\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n*   `warmup_ms = 25`: Run for 25ms to warm up the GPU before timing\r\n*   `rep_ms = 100`: Run for 100ms to collect timing data\r\n~~~\r\n\r\nI used 4096 as a fixed hidden dimension, chosen b/c that is the size for llama3-8b.  \r\nResults below are on B200. \r\n\r\n\r\nForward:\r\n<img width=\"581\" height=\"86\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 11 13 50 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/129933b4-7f98-467d-a061-a606743e4fef\" />\r\n\r\nBackward:\r\n<img width=\"593\" height=\"113\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 9 58 20 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a2b928f6-8744-4b22-905f-e0b2d5ee4110\" />\r\n\r\nI've added memory tracking as well to provide another dimension:\r\nForward:\r\n<img width=\"582\" height=\"129\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 11 27 19 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bbe67b3e-d3e7-4135-b189-6bd3ab51be0f\" />\r\n\r\nBackward:\r\n<img width=\"582\" height=\"129\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 11 26 52 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dfef231c-3b2b-4736-8c9a-06fb2fad1e18\" />\r\n\r\nResults are both tabular:\r\n~~~\r\nBatch Size: 8, Sequence Length: 8192, Hidden Size: 4096\r\n+--------------+--------------+---------------+----------------------+-----------------+-----------+\r\n|   Batch Size |   Seq Length |   Hidden Size | Implementation       |   Avg Time (ms) | Speedup   |\r\n+==============+==============+===============+======================+=================+===========+\r\n|            8 |         8192 |          4096 | PyTorch RMSNorm      |          3.2852 | 1.00x     |\r\n+--------------+--------------+---------------+----------------------+-----------------+-----------+\r\n|            8 |         8192 |          4096 | TorchCompile RMSNorm |          0.2556 | 12.85x    |\r\n+--------------+--------------+---------------+----------------------+-----------------+-----------+\r\n|            8 |         8192 |          4096 | Quack RMSNorm        |          0.1958 | 16.78x    |\r\n+--------------+--------------+---------------+----------------------+-----------------+-----------+\r\nQuack vs PyTorch Speedup: 16.78x\r\nQuack vs TorchCompile Speedup: 1.31x\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n\r\nand visual (under the 'visual_outputs' dir). \r\nForward:\r\n<img width=\"1129\" height=\"482\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 11 16 57 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/da99b156-4162-4672-bf88-78ee28c2ba46\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1129\" height=\"482\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 11 17 14 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cb0d02f6-bace-46a9-a85c-534c3a66eaaa\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nBackwards:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"836\" height=\"353\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 10 03 22 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/020bd984-6f11-4383-9cdb-411e6a145de6\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"937\" height=\"394\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-07-16 at 10 03 06 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d42cd7e1-b22d-4645-b473-c1f8c63868ee\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
